The article summarizes a press conference held by President Obama, President Calderon of Mexico, and Prime Minister Harper of Canada. The leaders discussed various topics including the economy, health, security, and immigration reform. They emphasized the importance of working together to restore economic growth, combat organized crime, address climate change, and protect human rights. President Obama expressed his commitment to comprehensive immigration reform and stated that the US has not intervened enough in Honduras to restore democratic order. Prime Minister Harper discussed the "Buy American" provisions and the need for a uniquely American approach to healthcare reform. Overall, the leaders highlighted the importance of cooperation and collaboration among the three North American countries.